inn1.comm: started off with a good length delivery, angling down the leg side and Farhat gets hit on the pad. Half hearted appeal for lbw turned down
the ghost is still around. Last match the West Indies bowlers gave away 32 extras and Bradshaw has started the counter today with a wayward delivery outside the off stump
good length delivery outside the off stump. Farhat gets behind the line and defends it with a straight bat
on the middle and off stump line. Farhat pushes forward and the ball rolls away off the inside edge to the square leg region
on the middle and leg stump line, Afridi is bit early into the shot and the ball spoons up on the leg side. Awkward looking shot in the end
finds the gap between mid-on and cover. Afridi off the mark with an easy single - huge cheers all around - they just love to see him bat.
good delivery to end the over. Farhat gets well forward and defends it down watchfully
another wide - Powell goes way down the leg side, 'nothing new' some would say.
good length delivery outside the off stump, hint of movement away from the right-hander
much better line and length. In the channel and shaping away - Afridi reads it well and leaves it through to the keeper
beauty and the ball zips past the outside edge - Afridi was clueless there

bowled'm! Powell strikes early - Peach of a leg-cutter. Pitched on an around the middle stump and shaping away, Afridi plays all over it and the ball crashes into the woodwork. Looking to play across the line to a ball that was shaping away. Crowd goes mute and Afridi walks back counting the grass.
left alone outside the off stump
good delivery to end the over - Hammed leaves it through to the keeper
forced away towards point, nicely played
beaten outside the off stump, hint of away swing
defended down to dilly mid-on
good length delivery outside the off stump, shaping away, Farhat shoulders arms
driven wide of the fielder at cover, quick single taken
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, defended watchfully
good length delivery outside the off stump, Farhat gets well forward and drives it down to mid-off, calls for the single but Hameed sends him back
line and length delivery, defended with a straight bat
fiery bouncer and Farhat ducks under it - one for the over called
drifting onto middle and leg, ball rolls away off the pad and they scamper through for a single
left alone outside the off stump
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, Hammed shoulders arms and the ball sails through to the keeper
slightly short and drifting down the leg side - Farhat shuffles across a bit and tucks it away straight to the fielder at short fine leg - missed out there on some easy runs
short and wide outside the off stump, cut away behind point for a single
drifting into the pads from wide outside the leg stump. Hameed stays back and works it away towards square leg. Fielder attacks the ball from the edge of the circle and cuts off the single
this one nipped back and Hammed is all at sea, ball clips the pad and pops up behind the stumps on the off side
good length delivery. The one that goes straight on - Hameed gets behind the line and defends it hard into the track
another wide! good length delivery, pitched outside the off stump and angling across - bit of a harsh call this
defended on the front-foot
worked away behind square on the leg side, easy single
on the middle and off stump line. Hameed moves across and works it away towards midwickets -  dangerous shot
worked away off the pads to the square leg region - fumble in the deep by Bradshaw gives away an extra run
good length delivery outside the off stump, hint of away swing and Hameed is beaten outside the off stump
and again, another ripper outside the off stump and the ball goes past the outside edge. Hameed once again beaten by the away movement there
good length delivery outside the off stump, hint of away swing and Farhat leaves it through to the keeper
short of a good length delviery outside the off stump - this one went straight on. Farhat reads it well and leaves it through to the keeper
goodness me - another extra, this time it's a no-ball

bit of frustration creeping in - good length delivery outside the off stump. Farhat comes down the track and swing hard, not sure what he was trying to achieve there. Gets nowhere near the line and the ball zips past the outside edge
wrong line from Bradshaw. Drifting down the leg side and the Farhat turns it away straight to the fielder at short fine leg - again misses out on an easy scoring chance
steered down to third man for an easy single - much better shot from the left-hander. Waited for the ball and opened the face of the bat at the last possible moment
and it gets worse - another wayward delivery down the leg side.
short of a good length delivery - Hameed fails to make contact and the ball rolls away off the pad
forced away towards cover and they sprint acroos for a single. excellent running between the wickets
good length delivery outside the off stump. Hammed watches it all the way into the keeper's gloves
wrong line and length. Bit too full and on the pads - Hameed waits for the ball and nicely turns it away through the vacant square leg region
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, bit of extra bounce there. Hameed shoulders arms
another wide! Lara is looking more like the gardener at the cemetery - he has lots of people under him, but nobody is paying him any attention. For the record this one way way outside the off stump
left alone outside the off stu8mp
forced away off the back-foot to the cover reigon, no room for a single there
good length delivery on the middle and leg stump line  - Farhat looking to flick it away on the leg side ends up with a thick inside edge
again plays away on the leg side, better timed on this occasion
and Farhat finally cashes in - good length and drifting down the leg side. Farhat shuffles across, gets well inside the line and works it away wide of the fielder at short fine leg
cut away off the back-foot, easy single to deep backward point
good length delivery on the stumps, worked away straight to the fielder at midwicket. Dangerous shot to play - if he misses, that's it then
shot. clipped away off the pads and Hameed gets it well in front of square leg. End of a good over for Pakistan
nudged away well wide of the fielder at midwicket, runs hard and comfortably comes back for the second
good length delivery outside the off stump, left alone outside the off stump
another good delivery outside the off stump. In the channel and shaping away - Hammed watchfully leaves it through to the keeper
turned away straight to the fielder at short square leg
good length delivery and this one nipped back in sharply - Hameed pushes forward to defend and ends up with an inside edge onto the pad
good length delivery outside the off stump and Hameed taps it away towards cover
good length delivery, right in the channel and shaping away late. Farhat is beaten on the forward prod
short of a good length delivery, close to the off stump line. Farhat leans back and cuts late - easy single down to third man

a no-ball, now that's a rarity! god length delivery, pitched close to the off stump line and angling across. Hameed is sucked forward into the drive and the ball races away off the outside edge to the third man region
makes room and swing across the line - end up with a thick inside edge onto his pad.
cut away nicely to the point region - Diving stop by Smith there cuts off runs
drifting onto middle and leg, Farhat fails to connect and the ball rolls away off the pad
cut away off the back-foot to the third man region, bit of edge involved
and the extras continues to mount, they are going for the record - no doubt. good length delivery down the leg side, Farhat goes for the flick but fails to make contact
hit on the pad

gone! short and wide outside the off stump - 'the sucker ball' as the call it in Australia. Farhat goes for the cut and fails to keep it down, Gayle at gully times his jump to perfection and takes it high over his head. Only Gayle could have taken that as it was hit pretty high
nudged down to third man for a single - Hafeez off the mark straightaway
left alone outside the off stump
bit of extra bounce and Hammed is beaten outside the off stump  - awkward looking drive of the back-foot
driven off the back-foot and he gets it away through point for a single
short and wide outside the off stump, cut away off the back-foot to the third man region
Et tu Smith! wayward delivery outside the off stump, hint of swing but what is the use
square driven straight to the fielder at point
left alone otuside the off stump - much better line and length
nice shape away and Hafeez is beaten outside the off stump - well bowled
good length delivery, Smith once again getting the ball to shape away from the right-hander. Hafeez shoulders arms
no shot offered - apart from the wide a good over
pitched up and shaping away - Hameed is sucked forward into the drive and the ball rips past the outside edge
short ball and Powell goes for the pull, not a well timed shot and the ball just about clears the fielder at mid-on
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven straight to the fielder at cover
take that! Powell once again drags it short and this time Hameed pulls it well over the fielder at midwicket. Got right on top of the bounce and placed it to perfection. Good positive shot
excellent comeback, full and swinging away - Hammed goes for the drive, eyeing cover and the ball goes through to the keeper
driven away through cover point - two more added to the total

edged and gone! good length delivery, pitched outside the off stump and swinging away - looked like a harmless delivery. Hafeez pushes forward to defend and the edge is produced. Gayle at second slip takes a good low catch. Pakistan three down and in a spot of bother here
good length delivery and this one came in with the angle, Malik gets behind the line and defends it well - excellent delivery first up
edged but short - Malik too troubled by the out swinger there - played it with soft hands and the ball fell well shot of Lara at first slip
driven straight to the fielder at mid-on
defended on the back-foot
pitched up and drifting in, driven straight back past the bowler to the mid-on region. Another successful over comes to an end.
drifting onto the pads, was there to be hit but Hameed fails to make contact.
good length delivery outside the off stump, well left
good length delivery outside the fof stump - Hameed gets a good stride in and drives it straight to the fielder at cover. Solid shot but the placement was poor
edged away well wide of the fielder at second slip, another good out swinger from Powell
on the middle and off stump line. Malik hops into position and clips it away straight to the fielder at midwicket
good length but bit wide outside the off stump. Malik on 'safe mode' leaves it through to the keeper

driven off the back-foot and Hameed gets it away into the gap between mid-on and midwicket. Simmons at mid-on hurtles across to his leg - dives across full length and saves runs. Excellent effort from the young man
punched away towards cover
driven back to the bowler, Malik not in full control there
forced away towards cover point and there is a big mix-up going for the single. Morton there fails to pick it up cleanly and both the batsmen rush back to safety
defended to cover
got'm! full and swinging in. Malik plays down the wrong line and is struck on the pad - that's plumb and up goes the finger
called for over-stepping. If only they could cut this flow of extras.
good length delivery outside the off stump, defended
frustration - comes down the track and swings hard, ball clips the top of the bat and spoons up over the fielder at mid-off
driven straight to the fielder at cover
defended on the back-foot - watchfully played
gets forward and pushes it to covers
driven down to mid-on for an easy single
fulltoss outside the off stump - missing was the gift wrap. Iqbal hammers it through extra cover
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, steered down to third man for an easy single
again short and way outside the off stump, umpire too tired and Smith gets away with it
good length delivery outside the off stump. Iqbal gets a good stride in and defends it with a straight bat
bit wide outside the off stump. Iqbal gets well forward, lines it up nicely and glides it down to third man for single - opened the face of the bat at the point of impact to get the placement right
worked away well wide of the fielder at mid-on
good length delivery outside the off stump, Iqbal pushes forward to defend but pulls away at the last moment
punched off the back-foot to the cover region, fielder moves in quickly and cuts off the single
short of a good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, angling across - Hameed shuffles across, gets right behind the line and defends it down on the leg side
came in from outside the leg side, Hameed looking to work it away on the leg side is beaten
short of a good length delivery on the middle and off stump line. Hameed defends on the back-foot and the ball rolls away off the inside edge
pitched up wide outside the off stump. Hameed quickly transfers his weight onto the front-foot and zaps it through cover point - a much needed boundary for Pakistan
left alone outside the off stump
short of a good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, defended on the back-foot
forced away towards point
again on the middle and off stump line, defended on the back-foot and the ball rolls away square on the off side
short and drifting down the leg side - by the time Iqbal started the pulls shot the ball had already reached the keeper
in the channel outside the off stump, defended on the front-foot
wicket to wicket delivery, worked away towards square leg
reared off a good length - Iqbal stands tall and defends it away towards cover point
defended back to the bowler
fuller in length and angling across - Hameed, looking to drive on the up ends up with a thick edge and the ball rolls away off the inner half of the bat
driven off the back-foot to the cover region
pitched up wide outside the off stump and angling across - Iqbal goes after it and the ball goes through to the keeper. Close to being a wide
driven down to mid-off

short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, angling across. Iqbal leans back, makes room and cuts hard - played it late and he finds the gap between point and gully. Diving effort in the deep from Powell ends in vain
left alone outside the off stump
steered down to third man for an easy single
good length delivery, cutting in. Iqbal waits for the ball and works it away well wide of the fielder at midwicket
good length delivery outside the off stump, tapped away straight to the fielder at mid-off
width offered outside the off stump and Hammed goes hard at it - ball clips the outside edge and flies over the fielder at gully
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump. Iqbal shoulders arms and leaves it through to the keeper
defended on the back-foot
bowled from over the stumps and on the pads, turned away well in front off square leg
tossed up and this one lands full outside the leg stump - Hameed goes low and sweeps it away fine
good length and on the middle and leg stump line, defended
pitched up outside the off stump, driven down to long-off
again full and outside the off stump - Iqbal gets forward and drives it down to long-off
short rising delivery outside the off stump, no shot offered
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven hard but straight to the fielder at cover

good length delivery on the pads, Iqbal leans well forward and clips it away towards fine leg - Simmons' has a go at the bowler's end from the deep - had he hit we could have woken up the third umpire
defended outside the off stump
driven off the back-foot and the ball rolls away through cover point
punched off the back-foot, ball rolls down to mid-on and they scamper through for a single
tossed up on the pads, defended
driven down to long-on for an easy single
bit wide outside the off stump, Iqbal rocks back and cuts it away towards point
on the middle and off stump line, flat delivery - Iqbal gets well forward and defends it with a straight bat
worked away through square leg for an easy single
full and drifting down the leg side, Hameed goes for the sweep and gets hit on the pad - another quick over from Mohammed comes to an end
edged and dropped - good length delivery outside the off stump, hint of shape away and the edge is produced - Ramdin fails to hold on to a fairly easy chance. Not that it would have counted
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, Iqbal leaves it through to the keeper - now that's a safe shot
again left alone outside the off stump
steered away straight to Gayle at gully
pitched wide and shaping away, Iqbal drives away from his body and the ball goes through to the keeper - needless shot
line and length delivery outside the off stump, defended stretching well forward
slower delivery to end the over - close to a wide but not called
cut away off the back-foot to the third man region
pitched up outside the off stump, driven down to long-off
full and drifting down the leg side, swept away straight to the fielder at short fine leg
full and close to the off stump line, Hameed gets well forward and defends it down on the leg side
excellent line and length, bit of extra turn and the ball pops up off the leading edge
forced away through square for a single
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump - defended
slow off-cutter and the ball rolls away off the inner half of the bat to the midwicket region - sloppy fielding gives away an extra run
driven on the up to the point region, bit of edge involved
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line. Hameed leans forward and clips it away through midwicket for a single
driven down to long-on for a single
pitched up outside the off stump and Iqbal goes hard at it - ball clips the outside edge and rolls down to third man, again just a single
edged and through - tossed up outside the off stump - Iqbal pushes forward to defend and is beaten by the extra bounce. Ramdin fails to hold on to a fairly hard chance
worked away through midwicket, runs hard looking for the second but the fielder moves in quickly from the deep and cuts it off
short ball and Iqbal cuts off the back-foot. Ball clips the outside edge and races away well wide of Chanderpaul at short third man
better line and length, defended on the back-foot
worked away off the back-foot - easy single down to short third man
tight delivery, defended on the back-foot
slightly short and on the middle and off stump line. Iqbal rocks back and pulls it away to the backward square leg fence - lovely shot
shuffles across and runs it down to fine leg for a single
pitched up on the pads, clipped away to fine leg for a single
better line and length, defended down on the leg side and they scamper through for a single. Iqbal was bit late to take off but made it across safely in the end
again worked down to fine leg for a single - End of a fine spell from Smith
tossed up outside the off stump, defended on the front-foot
turned away off the pads to deep sqaure leg
flat delivery on the stumps, punched down to long-off for a single
tossed up on the stumps - bit of a surprise delivery and Hameed defends it with a straight bat
driven straight back to the bowler - well bowled
full and on the pads, driven away through the gap between mid-on and midwicket
That's the fifty. Scratchy to start off but he fought on
short of length, just outside off, steered to point

Gotcha! Banged in short and Iqbal pulled but found the man at long leg. Mohammed judged it perfectly, his feet were dangerously close to the ropes but he balanced himself, and took the catch. Pretty good innings from Iqbal comes to an end
shortish, outside off, punched to deep point
in the zone outside off, Razzaq shaped up to play but withdrew his bat from the line of the ball at the last minute, let it go through to the 'keeper
on the middle, worked away to midwicket
on the leg, turned behind square leg
drifting on the legs, tickled behind but the square-leg fielder rushes across to make the stop.
on the off and middle, pushed back down the track
lands on middle. spins away down leg. Wide called
lands on middle, turns in , attempted flick shot makes no contact, the ball rolls off the pads.. to the leg side
turning in from outside off, Razzaq goes back, punches it to cover
114.4 kph slower delivery to start off the procedings after the drinks break, around the offstump line, pushed back down the track
banged short in length, pulled to the left of deep midwicket
full, on the middle, biffed away but straight to mid-on. timing was awry that time
Another slower ball, 106.4 kph, delivery, full in length, on the leg and middle, tickled to fine leg
Violence! Hammed waltzes down the track, backs away from the leg stump in the process and slaps the fullish delivery through extra cover.
full, on the offstump line, pushed past point. Razaq is off the mark. Runs hard to come back for two
on the middle, turns in, worked to midwicket
fuller, on the leg and middle, Hameed gets on to the front foot, works it with the spin towards fineleg
shout for lbw as a fullish delivery, quicker and flatter at that, raps Razzaq on the pads. But it was going down.
pushed past cover
full in length, lands just outside off, turns in, Razzaq crouches, punches it past cover point
floated on the off and middle, Hameed leans forward, drives it to right of long-on and will get two
on the off and middle again, turns in, defended off the front foot
poor delivery but he gets away with it. outside leg, swept to backward short leg
leans forward, drives through extra cover
tossed up, on the off, slower through the air, Razzaq leans forward, waits for the ball to arrive, drives to long-off. Good ball and good shot.
outside off, driven through the offside ring
spins down the leg side.
outside off, full in length, leans forward to drive back to the bowler
full and on the off and middle, driven to right of long-on
full, on the middle, Razzaq works his wrist overtime, whips it past square-leg
lovely delivery. well flighted, on the middle and leg, Hameed is bit early in his drive, ends up sccoping it in the air, through mid-on, down to long-on
full, on the middle, slightly quick through the air, turned to the man behind squareleg
he is changing his pace pretty well. Again slower through the air, just outside off, looped up above Razzaq' eyeline, dipped, pushed back down the track
edged to thirdman region. It was a offspinner that didn;t spin much! just outside off and Hameed tried to whip it across the line but ....
spins from outside off, Hameed keeps his left foot across, turns teh delivery to behind square-leg
Goes for the slogsweep but doesn't connect. The ball rolls off the pads to the offside
fullish, on the off and middle, driven down the ground to long on
turns in after landing on a length just outside off, punched back to the bowler
comes down the pitch, drives to long-on

Lovely delivery. Razzaq charged down the track, not only did Mohammed drag back the length, but also changed the pace, lovely slower delivery and that one went the other way. Razzaq adjusted to push it past point
Mohammed gets the breakthrough. Short in length, and Hameed pulled it but straight down the throat of deep midwicket
just outside off, steered to point
floated up, on the middle, driven back to the bowler
tossed up, slower through the air, pushes it outside off, Akmal is made to reach for it, he does and pushes it through cover point
spins in from outside off, is rapped on the pads as he attempts to turn to on side
just outside off, spins in, Akmal waits for it to arrive, dabs through the vacant slip region

A mix-up and almost fatal. It was flighted well outside off, Akmal leans on to his front foot, drives to backward point. Razzaq charges down the track but Akmal is not interested in the single and sends him back. The throw comes in from Gayle but Razzaq makes it
tossed up outside off, driven square past point
floated outside off, and a lovely square-drive from Akmal and it will be his first boundary
poor delivery but Akmal fails to make use of it. Rank short delivery that turns in slightly and Akmal shapes for a violent pull cum slog, doesn't connect and is rapped on the pads
Paddle swept to Lendl Simmons at fineleg. Akmal thinks he can make it for two runs, runs hard but Simmons fires in a fast and accurate throw and that's that.
on the offstump line, defended off the front foot
And again. only this time, Naved opens the face of the bat in an effort to push it through the offstide, but gets a leading edge and the ball rolls to the offside
Ripper! Wrong'un. The chinaman had the Pakistani there. Landed on the leg stump line, Naved went back and it just ripped across him and he was completely caught by surprise
on the middle and leg, turned to midwicket
full, lands outside off, turns in, Razzaq goes for a late cut, pulls it off but finds the man behind point on the off side
spins in, beats the intended whip across the line, raps him on the pads
short of length, turns in from outside off, punched to cover
on the middle, spins in, Razzaq goes back , whips it past squareleg
After being made to feel a bit sheepish in the last bal of the previous over, Naved hits back in vengeance. He charges down the track, and swings a tossed-up delivery over long-off.
Awesome whack! Naved charges out again, backs away from the leg stump in the process, and slaps it through extra cover.
on the middle and leg, turned past squareleg
short in length, spins in, Razzaq presses back, opens up his stance and pulls
just outside off, late cut past point
quicker one, outside off but Razzaq is upto it. He backs away and cuts it fine, past point.
swing and a miss. Outside off, flatter one and Razzaq tries to to go over the offside ring, doesn't connect
on the off and middle, slog swept imperiously over midwicket.
outside off, swatted to long off
biffed to long-on
clever slower ball, delivered from round the wickets, full in length and Naved checked his shot, got an outside edge which took the ball towards thirdman region
Low full toss, drifting on the legs, and Razzaq doesn't need any invitation to indulge in plunder. He swings it to the deep midwicket region.
will retain the strike with a drive down to long-off
slow through the air, on the middle, Razzaq backs away, heaves it to deep midwicket. Lara has three men on the boundary on the leg side
outside off, short in length, cut past point
on the middle and leg, swept on a bent knee.
fires in a yorker, Razzaq is surprised by the length and the pace and is rapped on the pads as he pulls out of a slog sweep
Another attempted yorker, ends up drifting just outside leg, Razzaq does well to move to the middle stump and it runs to the fineleg boundary
slower through the air, Razzaq is early into his stroke but manages to push it through the mid-on region

Accidental run out!  Razzaq drives a full-length delivery back to the bowler, Bradshaw tries to grab it, and the ball eludes his palms, bounds off and where does it go? Pings the stumps at the non-striker's end and Naved is caught out of his crease

short and wide, cut to point. Good diving stop by Samuels, he fires in a throw at the non-striker's end - that is where all the action is happening this over, misses. else Sami would be back in the hutch. A overthrow results
outside off, dabbed past point
Razzaq falls while going for a six. He takes his left foot out of the line of a full-length delivery, and swings it over midwicket but couldn't clear the deep midwicket fielder.
slower ball, 109.3 kmph, full in length, he picked that one well, scooped it over mid-off
Almost caught by Samuels who was running backwards from point. It was a fullish delivery, outside off, tried to whip it across the line, gets a leading edge which takes the ball over point
down the legside, swept fine
on the middle, turned to square-leg
floated on the middle and leg, flicked over square-leg
Slow through the air, Anjum is through his slog sweep a bit early and ends up shovelling it to Smith who runs in from long-leg to take the catch.

inn2.comm: starts off with a good ball on the middle and off stump line, hint of swing and Gayle plays it away on the leg side
short of a good length delivery, came back in a touch? Gayle shuffles across a bit and defends it down on the off side
good length delivery outside the off stump, Gayle leaves it through to the keeper
pitched up further and close to the off stump line, teasing delivery but Gayle ignores it and the ball goes through to the keeper
hint of swing back in and the edge is produced but the ball falls well short of the fielder at second slip

good length and once again the ball shaped back in, Gayle ends up with a thick edge on the forward prod and the ball races away through the gap between gully and third slip - end of an excellent first over
pitched up outside the off stump and Gayle drives it straight to the fielder at mid-off. Powerful shot but the placement was poor
short of a good length delivery, pitched close to the off stump line and angling across - Gayle has a poke at it and the ball sails through to the keeper. Sami right on target here
and this one swung back in - Gayle completely misread it and the ball thuds into the pad
wrong line - drifting onto the pads and Gayle daces it away to the backward square leg fence, all he had to do was beat the fielder at short fine leg and the placement was spot on
four more - good length delivery on the middle and leg stump line, bit of inside edge involved and the ball races away through square leg
good length delivery outside the off stump, defended
short of a good length and angling across. Chanderpaul shuffles across a long way and defends it down
piched up and Chanderpual drives it away towards cover - slightly fumble and they scamper through for a single
defended outside the off stump

Rana strikes! full and swinging in. Gayle stands his ground and hits across the line and the ball crashes into the off stump. Pakistan off to an excellent start here - that's the wicket they needed to make a match out of it.

that's the end of that! Rana on a roll here - good length delivery on the stumps, this one straightened after hitting the deck - Simmons was done in by the extra pace and the angle. Easy decision for the umpire as Simmons was caught plumb in front. Naved-ul-Hasan is on a hat-trick here.
good length delivery outside the off stump, came back in a touch but Samuels gets right behind the line and defends it down safely - end of a fantastic over for Pakistan
left alone outside the off stump
short of a good length and angling across, Chanderpaul leaves it through to the keeper
Sami goes wider outside the off stump and the umpire is not amused
short of a good length delivery, in the channel and angling across - Chanderpaul leaves it through to the keeper
short of a good length and this one came back in, excellent delivery - Chanderpaul was clueless and the ball hits him high on the pad. Half hearted appeal turned down. Clearly going over the stumps
pitched up on the pads and Chanderpaul clips it away well wide of the diving Afridi at backward square leg - welcome boundary for West Indies
better line and length, left through to the keeper
on the pads, worked away towards fine leg for an easy single
pitched up and swinging away - that was a talking delivery but the line was wrong
bit wide outside the off stump and this one curled back in after passing the stumps
in the channel outside the off stump, defended watchfully
short of a good length - this one hits the seam and nips back in sharply. Chanderpaul shuffles across a long way, gets right behind the line and defends it with a straight bat
pitched up and shaping back in. Chanderpaul waits for the ball to swing and then drives it through the gap between mid-on and midwicket. Perfect timing and Razzaq at mid-on quickly gave up the chase
slightly short and outside the off stump - Chanderpaul walks across and defends it carefully
wayward delivery outside the off stump
short ball outside the off stump. Chanderpaul caught in two minds and in the end it was a nothing pull - ball rolls straight to the fielder at mid-off
good length delivery, shaping away and Samuels is turned inside out - Sami too is looking dangerous
pitched up and swinging away. Samules goes for the drive and the ball shapes away from the bat - missed the edge by a whisker. Close call
down the leg side
short of a good length delivery on the stumps - Samules stands tall on the back-foot and defends it down on the leg side
bit wide but once again the ball swung away from the right-hander - Samuels leaves it through to the keeper
again left alone outside the off stump
wide outside the off stump and Samuels leaves it through to the keeper
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, defended on the front-foot
swinging in, Chanderpaul wlaks across and defends it
slower delivery, bit too full and that made it much more complicated, but Chanderpaul nicely got behind the line and presented the full face of the bat
left alone outside the off stump
another well disguised slower delivery - this one went on with the angle and Chanderpaul is beaten outside the off stump
worked away towards midwicket, no room for a single there
pitched up outside the off stump, driven well but straight to the fielder at cover
good length delivery outside the off stump. Samules goes right back and defends it well
drifting down the leg side, ball clips the pad and rolls down to the fine leg region
pitched up and swinging in, driven straight to the fielder at midwicket
another fuller length delivery, This one was pitched on middle and off and was angled across the left-hander. Chanderpaul had no option but to play at it and was beaten all ends up
sigh...another Sami wide - again way down the leg side
good length delivery on the middle and leg stump line. Chanderpaul waits for the ball to swing and softly plays it away towards square leg
bouncer - on and around the off stump line - Samules leans back and leaves it through to the keeper
not again! Rana struggling a bit here - another wide down the leg side
hits the grove and that's a fantastic line to the right-hander. In the channel and shaping away late. Samuels pushes forward to defend and the ball zips past the outside edge
defended outside the off stump
and he drifting down the leg side. Samules fails to make contact but the ball clips the pad and races away to the fine leg fence
defened to covers - solid shot
good length delivery outside the off stump, steered down to third man for a single
short rising delivery outside the off stump. Samules stands tall and leaves it through to the keeper
harmless wide delivery outside the off stump - can't balme the umpire must be Earth's gravitation&
take that! good length delivery outside the off stump. width offered outside the off stump and Samules drills it through the gap between the cover fielder. Try stopping that
worked away towards square leg
defended on the back-foot. again the ball rolls away towards square leg and this time they scamper through for a single
defended outside the off stump
pitched up outside the off stumps and Chanderpaul drives it straight back to the bowler

drifting onto the pads, Rana clearly struggling here now. Samuels clips it away with a hint of artistry to the fine leg region - looked like a certain boundary but Rao hurtled across in the deep and kicked the ball in from right in front of ropes - excellent effort
anothet wide - this is so frustrating. just for the record this one was again down the leg side
clipped away to fine leg for an easy single
for a change this one is way outside the off stump - Rana is struggling to control the swing here. He started off well but now...
defended outside the off stump, ball rolls away towards cover
again played away towards cover, Rana has cut down on pace here - that's good thinking
slower delivery outside the fof stump and Samuels is beaten outside the off stump
low fulltoss, slower delivery gone wrong - Samules watis for the ball and taps it away on the leg side. Early call and they scamper through for a single
pitched up and Samules drives it straight back to the bowler
short and wide outside the off stump and Samuels cuts it past the fielder at gully - Afridi in the deep makes a mess of things and the ball rolls over the ropes.
shot! good length delivery outside the off stump and Samuels drives it through cover. Classy shot. Made it look easy
punched down to mid-on, easy single
defended outside the off stump
short of a good length delivery, close to the off stump line - Chanderpaul gets right on top of the bounce and taps it away on the leg side
short and turning away, defended on the back-foot

pitched up on the stumps, right in the slot and Samuels thuds it straight back down the track to the long-on fence. pre4sented the full face of the bat and the placement was just spot on. Mid-on had no chance of cutting it off

four more! Samuels is making batting look easy out there and he is doing it in style. Tossed up and turning away, Samuels plunges forward to the pitch of the delivery and caresses it through extra cover. The fielder at Long-off did make an effort to get to the ball but ...
defended on the front-foot
tossed up, watchfully played away
forced away towards cover
good length delivery outside the off stump, defended on the front-foot
steered away towards third man and they comfortably makes it back for the second
good length delivery outside the off stump, defended
good length delivery on the pads, no sigh of swing there - Chanderpaul nicely works it away well in front of square leg and this time they come back for the third
short of a good length delivery, cutting in - Samules gets behind the line and defends it well
ripper of a delivery to finish the over - Samuels is left searching for the ball - luckily for West Indies the ball missed the edge
punched back to the bowler
wrong'un - fuller length delivery outside the off stump and Chanderpaul goes for the big shot over mid-on, ball clips the top edge and spoons up over the fielder at cover
defended on the back-foot
quicker delivery, watchfully played away on the off side
juicy fulltoss outside the off stump and Samuels jabs is straight back down the track to the long-on fence. It's looking all too easy at the moment for West Indies
tossed up outside the off stump, better line and length - defended on the front-foot

driven away through cover point, bit of a mix-up going for the third run. Samules was half way down the track but Chanderpaul was not interested - Throw comes in at the wrong end and Samules makes it back safely
pitched up and angling across. Chanderpaul goes for the drive - ball clips the edge and screams away to the third man fence. Required run rate is melting - Pakistan badly need a wicket here
hit on the pad trying to work it away through midwicket
short and wide outside the off stump, Chanderpaul goes for the cut - ball clips the bottom edge and rolls away towards the slip cordon
left alone outside the off stump
worked away on the leg side, Anjum moves across quickly on his followthrough and cuts off the single
starts off with an off-cutter, defended on the front-foot
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, driven straight to the fielder at cover
driven off the back-foot, again straight to the man at cover
fuller length delivery, cutting in - Samules gets forward and drives it down to mid-on. Not a well timed shot and the ball came off the inner half of the bat
good length delivery outside the off stump, Samules is sucked forward into the drive and the ball goes straight to the fielder at mid-off.
bouncer down the leg side and that's a wide
swing and a miss outside the off stump - good delivery to end the over

short of a good length delivery, angling across the left-hander. Chanderpaul gets forward and square drives it through cover point. Malik gives chase but the ball wins the race. Almost pulled off an excellent save with his boot but he failed to stop the ball cleanly and once he had gone over the ropes the ball rolled forward and touched the rope
driven down to mid-off
short ball, pulled away well over the fielder at midwicket - West Indies racing away at this stage
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump. Chanderpaul too goes for the pull and gets it away to deep midwicket. Three more runs added to the total
Samuels goes bang! and the ball sails over the midwicket fence! short ball outside the off stump - pull shot played to perfection and the ball just sailed off the middle of the bat
lofted over the fielder at mid-on and they have amassed 21 runs off this over. This is attacking cricket at its best.
defended outside the off stump
defended outside the off stump, ball rolls away off the edge to the third man region
defended to cover, no room for a single there
driven wide of the fielder at mid-on
Razzaq is doing his bit - wayward delivery down the leg side
good length delivery outside the off stump. Chanderpaul is beaten on the forward prod
good length delivery outside the off stump - nothing wrong with the ball. Chanderpaul plunged forward to the pitch of the delivery and just caressed it through the gap between mid-off and cover.
tossed up outside the off stump, turned away towards the vacant square leg region for an easy single
drifting in with the arm, defended on the front-foot
bit of width offered outside the off stump, cut away straight to the fielder at point
fuller length delivery, driven straight to the fielder at point
inside edge and the ball rolls away towards midwicket - easy single added to the total
tossed up and turning in, worked away with the spin to the midwicket region

on the pads, too easy a delivery and Chanderpaul clips it away to the midwicket fence. Just the one fielder inside the circle on the leg side and Chanderpaul gave him no chance - boundary brings up the 100 partnership
good length delivery outside the off stump and Chanderpaul drills it through the gap between mid-off and cover - this now is the highest partnership of the series

on the rampage now! under pressure Razzaq drags it short and Chanderpaul dismisses it to the  midwicket fence - three fours in three ball and this is turning out to be another massive over for West Indies
and he oversteps
fifty! clipped away to long-leg for an easy single
defended outside the off stump
worked away off the pads to the fine leg region - 15 off the over.
fuller length delivery, driven down to long-on
turned away off the pads to the midwicket region
bowled from round the stumps and tossed up outside the off stump. Chanderpaul gets well forward and drives it down to long-off for an easy single
tucked away straight to the fielder at square leg
gets well forward and drives it straight down the track to the long-on region
flatter trajectory and drifting in with the arm, Chanderpaul gets well forward and drives it away towards cover
tossed up and turning in, driven straight to the fielder at cover

there it is. short delivery outside the off stump. Samuels goes right back and cuts it away towards cover - Hameed there fails to stop it cleanly and the batsmen cross over for a single - what an innings
driven straight to the fielder at point
tossed up on the pads, turned away straight to the fielder at short fine leg
fraction short and bit wide outside the off stump - Chanderpaul goes for the cut but fails to make contact. Akmal gets hit on the knee - that hurts
eased away on the leg side for an easy single
tossed up outside the off stump. Chanderpaul plays across the line and gets beaten by a long way. Akmal fails to collect it cleanly
driven down to mid-on. mix-up going for the single and Samules dives it at the keeper's end
fuller in length, driven down to long-on for an easy single&
drifting in with the arm, driven away towards cover
driven wide of the fielder at cover
worked away towards midwicket
just outside off, Chanderpaul waited for the ball to arrive, punched it to point
slow through the air, spins in from outside leg, pushed away
lands on the middle, turns away, Chanderpaul goes  back, punches it to long-off
floats from outside off, driven back to the bowler
tossed up, fuller, driven to cover
Super shot. tossed up outside off and Samuels was down the wicket in a flash and caressed the ball through extra cover
drifts in from outside off, Chanders tries to go across, edge takes the ball to point
fuller, on the blockhole almost, stabbed away towards mid-on and they rush across for a single
floated up, full, driven through mid-off, Rao makes a good diving half-stop, and deflects the ball to long-on
pushed back to the bowler
slower, held back the length a bit, turns away, Chanderpaul adjusts, runs it down to short thirdman
on the legs, tickled past squareleg
flighted delivery, around the middle and off, driven past cover
flighted again, just outside off, turns in, Samuels runs down the track, pushes it back to the bowler
good delivery. Flighted and it was slower through the air, Samuels was down the track, and was beaten in flight and is rapped on the pads
slightly short in length, outside off, turns in a touch, goes back to cut it past point
short again, allows Chanderpaul to sit back and swat it to long-off
Bad delivery and put away without any fuss. Well outside off and short as well, Samuels eased back, cut it past point
drifted in from round the stumps, pushed to cover point
flatter, on the middle and leg, cramped Samuels who shovels it to midwicket
flatter again, on the middle, Samuels plays for the spin, it isn't there and gets a leading edge to cover
goes back to a shortish ball, punches it to cover
lands outside off, spins back in sharply with bounce and Samuels who is trying to force it through off is surprised by the spin and adjusts to swat it away to midwicket
spears it down full and on the legs. Chanderpaul tries to flick but misses and the ball rolls away  off the pads.
short, on the off and middle, Samuels goes for the pull, doesn't time it well but manages to get it past midwicket
swing and a miss. Pushed across well outside off, Chanderpaul goes for a cut but the ball bounces over the blade
Got im! Short and on the hips, Chanderpaul plays a rather neat little pick-up pull shot but pings the man at fine-leg.  Some times it is not such a good idea to pick up!
full, furious, yorker, Lara stabs it away to point
strives for pace and ends up spearing it on the legs, attempted flick, runs off the pads
Lands on a length, moves across but so does Lara. In an exaggerated movement, he hops up, and back and across, and is squared-up while defending. The ball rolls away to the offside
ful, on the middle, pushed to Iqbal at mid-on. He fires in a direct hit but Lara makes his crease in time
Whack! Samuels stood up tall to a back-of-length delivery outside off that moved away, and forced it through extra cover
punched to mid-on and they hurry through for a single
ful-length delivery, around that off stump line, and Lara goes back, opens the face of the bat, runs it past the lone slip, down to thirdman

crashed into the pads. Another length delivery that landed on the middle and it jagged back in sharply, Samuels is surprised at the movement, takes the bottom-hand out of the handle, brings his blade down across the line and doesn't make contact.

Lovely shot for nothing.  Length delivery, just outside off,  punched through the line but can't beat cover. There was no foot movement, no back and across, he just stood there, bent a little, to spread the balance and went through with the shot
Ouch. A short of length delivery crashes into , off the inside edge, the inner thigh and that must have hurt

Dropped by Rana Naved.  Fullish delivery and Samuels tries to biff it down the ground, and it drops just in front of Naved at mid-off who tries to get his palm under the ball but doesn't manage to hold on
Lara had a chat with Samuels. Obviously he didn't say don't hit as this ball, Samuels took his left foot out of the line, opened up the stance and slapped a shortish delivery over midwicket
flick to square-leg
swing and a miss. Banged in short again and Samuels tries to swing it across, misses
Fab straight drive. Overpitched on the stumps, Samuels eases forward, caresses it straight down the ground.
Oho! Lara goes for the jugular, doesn't connect though. It was full and just outside off, Lara tried to hit through the line...
risky dab across the line. A length delivery that landed outside leg, came back in  a touch, Lara was hopping back and brings his bat down in an angle, manages ti get it past midwicket

Huge shout for a caught behind decision. Landed short of length, just outside off, came back in and Samuels tried to go swat it across the line, there was a sound, and Akmal who gathers it goes up in appeal...

Ah. Super straight drive. When he can play such shots, why does he go for those across the line swipes. Fullish, and Samuels presented the full face of the bat in his drive and pinged the straight boundary
in the zone outside off, slower delviery, left alone
full-length, Lara goes back rather than forward, stabs it away to the offside

Wah! Wah! Samuels is flowing like a river tonight. Imperious lofted drive. Full in length and Samuels just took out the left foot out of the line and creamed it, in the air , between the bowler and mid-on

Lovely comeback from Anjum. Slower deliv ery, on the stumps,  almost had Samuels who somehow adjusted at the last minute, stopped his intended lofted drive, and pushed the delivery away to the off side
full, outside off, Lara leans forward, opens the bat-face, steers it to right of point and Hafeez makes a good diving stop
length-delivery, outside off, Lara goes back and across, steers it to Hafeez at point
fullish, on the off and middle, Lara leans forward, slightly late, brings his bat down across the line, dabs the ball to midwicket
beaten. Ambitious heave outside the offstump. doesn't make contact . Lara goes across, has a chat with the youngster. Lets see what he does next ball
Ah....Length-delivery, lands on middle, came back in but Samuels adjust to that movement, whips it past midwicket
full in length, outside off, eased past cover
Banged in short, stands up on his toes, swivels and bang, To the deep midwicket boundary
That's his hundred, his second. Brought up in style.  Full and on the legs, clipped away powerfully. This has been such a dazzling knock.   Has Samuels finally arrived?
length-delivery, eased to cover point&
Orgasmic drive over cover! What a shot! It was a length delivery but Lara leant forward, and just drove on the up. Elegant, Imperious and Languid.
And that great shot is followed up with a ugly swipe! Banged in short and Lara tries to slap it across but doesn't connect
And that's it. West Indies have won their first game on this tour. Full, angled across, Lara leans forward, head over the ball, square-drives it past point.
